text: Bargata () is a rural locality (a village) in Uchpilinsky Selsoviet, Dyurtyulinsky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 111 as of 2010. There are 2 streets. == Geography == It is located 29 km from Dyurtyuli. == References == Category:Rural localities in Dyurtyulinsky District
title: Bargata
